                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18201028-52-defend581 t18201028-52-deflabel301"></join>. On the 19th of October he left me. As he went out I saw a handkerchief on the ground, and asked if it was his? he said No, and went out. I made enquiry, set off to town, and took him at the Green Man and Still, Oxford-street, when the coach came in. He said he had robbed me, had on searching his box this property was found.</p>

